library(ggraph)
library(widyr)
library(gapminder)
set.seed(183)

Loads some data and make correlations

edges <- gapminder %>%
  select(country, year, lifeExp) %>%
  widyr::pairwise_cor(
    item = country,
    feature = year,
    value = lifeExp
  ) %>%
  filter(correlation > quantile(correlation, 0.99))
## Warning: Trying to compute distinct() for variables not found in the data:
## - `row_col`, `column_col`
## This is an error, but only a warning is raised for compatibility reasons.

nodes <- gapminder %>%
  select(country, continent) %>%
  distinct()
nodes
## # A tibble: 142 x 2
##    country     continent
##    <fct>       <fct>    
##  1 Afghanistan Asia     
##  2 Albania     Europe   
##  3 Algeria     Africa   
##  4 Angola      Africa   
##  5 Argentina   Americas 
##  6 Australia   Oceania  
##  7 Austria     Europe   
##  8 Bahrain     Asia     
##  9 Bangladesh  Asia     
## 10 Belgium     Europe   
## # ... with 132 more rows
net <- igraph::graph_from_data_frame(edges,
  vertices = nodes
) %>%
  as_tbl_graph() %>%
  mutate(cen = centrality_betweenness()) %>%
  filter(!node_is_isolated())
ggraph(net) +
  geom_edge_density(fill = "grey70") +
  geom_edge_link(aes(alpha = correlation)) +
  geom_node_point(aes(
    colour = continent,
    size = cen
  )) +
  geom_node_text(aes(label = name),
    repel = TRUE,
    check_overlap = TRUE
  ) +
  theme_graph() +
  theme(legend.position = "none") +
  labs(title = "Countries by pairwise correlation of Life Expectancy")
## Using `nicely` as default layout
